quote.p:
—U.S. side corrected Karpov’s statements that the U.S. side in
                                Geneva was insisting on explicit references to “transition” in the
                                    JDT;

—Karpov agreed the “agreement” and “protocol” could be worked in
                                parallel, but argued that the agreement should be completed first;
                                the U.S. side agreed to study the Soviet approach and try to work
                                with it, but insisted that the agreement and protocol would have to
                                be worked and finalized as a package;

—The Soviet verification measures approach is intended to support
                                such challenging approach in contrast to the U.S. predictability
                                measures approach;

—Karpov noted U.S. interest in a provision clarifying the WSJS
                                language by stating that the parties would agree not to argue about
                                the activities of sensors in space;
